&lt;h1 id="probability-is-subjective"&gt;Probability Is Subjective&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apr 16 2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Naval:&lt;/strong&gt;
Does probability actually exist in the physical universe, or is it a function of our ignorance? If I&amp;rsquo;m rolling a die, I don&amp;rsquo;t know which way it&amp;rsquo;s going to land; so therefore I put in a probability. But does that mean there&amp;rsquo;s an actual probabilistic unknowable thing in the universe? Is the universe rolling a die somewhere, or is it always deterministic?&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Explanations That Reach the Entire Universe</title><link>https://linguista.cn/naval/orig/explanations-that-reach-the-entire-universe/</link><pubDate>Mon, 08 Mar 2021 20:11:33 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/naval/orig/explanations-that-reach-the-entire-universe/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/naval/zh/explanations-that-reach-the-entire-universe.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
